    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey im working on my 2018 camry and just finished replacing the brake pads. but now when i take it out on the road i hear this really annoying high pitched squealing sound whenever i hit the brakes. not sure if its a sensor or if the caliper might be stuck or something. any idea what thats could be?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That high-pitched squeal after replacing the pads is a common, but frustrating, issue. It's often caused by vibrations between the new pads and the rotors, or sometimes by the brake pads themselves needing a bedding-in period. You could also check if the anti-rattle clips were installed correctly or if the calipers are binding up slightly. If the noise persists after driving a few hundred miles, a mechanic should inspect the hardware and rotor surface finish.",
      "source": "target",
