    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the clips and they seem fine. the sound is really sharp though, almost like metal on metal. could it be that the piston isn't retracting all the way? i'm worried it's a stuck caliper causing it. how can i tell for sure without taking the whole thing apart again?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A sharp, metal-on-metal sound definitely raises the concern that the caliper isn't seating or retracting properly. You can test this by observing the brake caliper while the vehicle is lifted safely; if you can see the piston moving unevenly or not fully seating back into its housing, that's a sign of a potential sticking caliper. If the sound is extremely sharp and persistent, it suggests improper pad seating or a caliper that is dragging, which should be inspected by a professional to prevent overheating and further damage.",
      "source": "target",
