    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it does feel like it's dragging a bit, the wheel feels hot after just a short drive. is there any way there could be something stuck in the mechanism? like some kind of debris or something that would cause that specific high pitch?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, debris is a very common culprit for that high-pitched, metal-on-metal squeal, especially if the caliper feels like it's dragging. Sometimes tiny bits of metal shavings from the old pads, or even some grit from the road, can get lodged between the caliper and pad assembly. Before diving into a full disassembly, try carefully inspecting the area around the caliper mounting points for any visible foreign objects. If you suspect debris, a thorough cleaning of the caliper bracket and mating surfaces is the next best step.",
      "source": "target",
